Opening paragraphs: tweaked structure to further clarify the difference between data dedup and single-instance storage. I have also made it clearer that a core advantage of reducing storage utilization is reduced expenditure on storage media - sounds obvious, I know, but a non-technical person reading this for some background info may not make that connection. Finally, added the clarification that when we talk about data 'chunks', we are referring to contiguous blocks.
